The paper deals with the problem of private information retrieval (PIR), which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of caches and side information suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The two-phase scheme and the need for privacy also suggest a connection to communication complexity (cs.CC).
